	of just in 'beginpage'.

2006-01-15  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* filters/gnome-print-filter-clip.c (beginpage_impl): gsave
	(showpage_impl): grestore. Like that, we reset the clip context for each new
	page.

2006-01-15  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* filters/gnome-print-filter-multipage.c: Simplify.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c: Simplify.

2006-01-12  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-job.c (gnome_print_job_setup_context): 
	Load filters from "Settings.Output.Job.Filter" (printer specific filters),
	"Settings.Document.Filter" (page selection, layout...) and
	"Settings.Document.Page.Layout" (for historic reasons).

2006-01-08  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* filters/gnome-print-filter-multipage.c
	* filters/gnome-print-filter-reorder.c
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c: Correct implementation of resetting
	and flushing filters.

2006-01-08  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* filters/gnome-print-filter-frgba.c: Just reset the meta data instead
	of recreating it on each beginpage.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c: Don't complain if there is no context.
	A previous filter may have suppressed the page. Just skip the command.

2006-01-04  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c (gnome_print_filter_reset): Fix small
	typo.

2006-01-04  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c (gnome_print_filter_clear_data): New.
	Use it in (gnome_print_filter_[finalize,reset]).

2006-01-02  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-filter.c (gnome_print_filter_reset): Don't unref
	the context - remove the weak pointer instead.

2006-01-01  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* tests/test-meta.c: New.
	* tests/Makefile.am: Hook it up. Remove some empty declarations.

2005-12-31  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

