2005-10-12  Lutz Mueller <lutz@topfrose.de>

	* filters/gnome-print-filter-reverse.[c,h]: New. Print in reverse order.
	* filters/Makefile.am: Hook up above files.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-job.c (gnome_print_job_print) : Only flush
	at the end of the document.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-ps2.c (gnome_print_ps2_close) : Just return
	if there are no pages to print. Don't warn.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print.c (gnome_print_context_close) : Flush filters
	before closing.

