	* libgnomeprint/filters/gnome-print-filter.[c,h]: Move up one directory.
	* libgnomeprint/filters/[grammar.y,parse.l,types.h]: Those files, too.
	* libgnomeprint/Makefile.am: Hook up above files
	* Makefile.am: Compile filters subdirectory
	* configure.in: Hook up filters subdirectory

2005-08-15  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* filters/*: Move files from libgnomeprint/filters/* here.

2005-08-15  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-job.c
	(gnome_print_job_setup_context): New. Creates necessary filters.
	(gnome_print_job_render): Simplify by using above function.

2005-08-15  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-job.c: Kill some warnings.

2005-08-14  Tor Lillqvist  <tml@novell.com>

	* libgnomeprint/filters/Makefile.am (install-exec-hook): Hack to
	make "make install" work, especially in tinderbox-like
	situations. See http://mail.gnome.org/archives/desktop-devel-list/2005-August/msg00110.html

	The real fix would be to change the source code organization of
	libgnomeprint to avoid the need to cd back and forth and run
	sub-makes. A suggestion: put libgnomeprintfilter in a directory of
	its own, as a sibling to libgnomeprint. The plugin modules should
	also be in a sibling directory to libgnomeprint, not a
	subdirectory of it. The top-level Makefile.am would have them in
	SUBDIRS in the order: libgnomeprintfilter, libgnomeprint,
	filters. I think the libs would then naturally build in the
	correct dependency order?

2005-08-11  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-ps2.c: Kill some warnings.
	(gnome_print_ps2_beginpage): Use gnome_print_clip_bpath_rule_real, thus
	avoiding all filter stuff at this level.

2005-08-10  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-private.h: Add GnomePrintContextPrivate to
	structure GnomePrintContext.
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print.c
	(gnome_print_context_[init,finalize]): Move up.
	(gnome_print_[[begin,show]page,gsave,grestore,[clip,fill]_bpath_rule,
	 stroke_bpath,[image,glyphlist]_transform): Redirect to filter if there is
	one.
	(gnome_print_set[rgbcolor,opacity,linewidth]): Move here from
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-stdapi.c
	(gnome_print_set[rgbcolor,opacity,linewidth]): Now in gnome-print.c.

2005-08-10  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* data/models/GNOME-GENERIC-PS.xml.in.in: The postscript driver needs the 
	FRGBA filter. Will be hooked up later in libgnomeprint/gnome-print-job.c.

2005-08-10  Lutz Mueller <lutz@users.sourceforge.net>

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-stdapi.c 
	(gnome_print_set[rgbcolor,opacity,linewidth]): Redirect call to filter if 
	there is one.
	(gnome_print_show), (gnome_print_show_sized): Kill warning.
	* libgnomeprint/filters/gnome-print-filter-multipage.c: Fix range.

2005-08-09  Tor Lillqvist  <tml@novell.com>

	* configure.in: Set SOEXT to .dll on Windows, .so on Unix. Expand
	the new files below.

	* data/models/GNOME-GENERIC-PS.xml.in
	* data/models/GNOME-META.xml
	* data/models/GNOME-PDF-WRITER.xml.in: Remove. Expand at
	configure time instead from the new .in files below.
	
	* data/models/GNOME-GENERIC-PS.xml.in.in
	* data/models/GNOME-META.xml.in
	* data/models/GNOME-PDF-WRITER.xml.in.in: Corresponding new
	files. Instead of hardcoding .so use @SOEXT@.

	* data/models/Makefile.am (models_in_files): Corresponding changes.

	Handle dependency mess intruduced recently, which causes problems
	on Win32 where -no-undefined really means what it says.

	* libgnomeprint/Makefile.am: As we now want to build
	libgnomeprint-2-2.la before the subdirs have been completely built
	(see below), add explicit dependency on gpa/libgpa.la,
	filters/libgnomeprintfilter.la and ttsubset/libttsubset.la, and
	add rule to cd to these subdirs and build these libs.
	(libgnomeprint_2_2_la_LIBADD): Put LIBGNOMEPRINT_LIBS last.
	
	* libgnomeprint/filters/Makefile.am: The plugin modules depend on
	../libgnomeprint-2-2.la and libgnomeprintfilter.la, so spell that
	out. Add rule to build ../libgnomeprint-2-2.la. Drop the
	LIBADD for libgnomeprintfilter.la. It is a noinst library,
	i.e. a static archive, so LIBADD is useless.

