2005-03-25  Ivan, Wong Yat Cheung <email@ivanwong.info>

	* configure.in: detection of win32

	* libgnomeprint/Makefile.am: include gnome-print-path.h and
	  the gdi drivers if host_os == win32.

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-font-face.c: italic_angle is counter-
	  clockwise on win32.

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-transport.c:
	* libgnomeprint/gpa/gpa-model.c
	* libgnomeprint/gpa/gpa-printer.c
	* libgnomeprint/gpa/gpa-root.c
	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-i18n.c: replace some path related
	  preprocessor definitions with global variables.

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print.c: fill path related global
	  variables on DLL_PROCESS_ATTACH, free them on
	  DLL_PROCESS_DETACH, this prevents leakage. Become more
	  robust when using CreateFileMapping()/MapViewOfFile().

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-path.h declare those global
	  variables.

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print.def: add back some missing
	  symbols, probably more.

	* libgnomeprint/gpa/gpa-printer.c (gpa_printer_new_from_tree):
	  lang was uninit if HAVE_LC_MESSAGES was not defined.

	* tests/fonts.c:
	* tests/generate.c:
	* tests/gpa-test.c:
	* tests/pango.c: make tests buildable with win32.

	* libgnomeprint/gnome-print-gdi.[ch]:
	* libgnomeprint/modules/Makefile.am:
	* libgnomeprint/modules/win32/Makefile.am:
	* libgnomeprint/modules/win32/gnome-print-win32-transport.c:
	* libgnomeprint/modules/win32/gnome-print-win32.c: introduce
	  the new win32 module for GP. Printer enumeration works,
	  more options could be added though. The transport class is dummy,
	  as gdi already handles those things. Have tested printing some
	  workbooks of gnumeric/samples/chat-tests.gnumeric and the outputs
	  seems okay. Should be able to improve the gstack/set_font as
	  CreateFont() is quite heavy.

